Literature.Author: Pandi A, Adam D, Zare A, Trinh VT, Schaefer SL, Burt M, Klabunde B, Bobkova E, Kushwaha M, Foroughijabbari Y, Braun P, Spahn C, Preußer C, Pogge von Strandmann E, Bode HB, von Buttlar H, Bertrams W, Jung AL, Abendroth F, Schmeck B, Hummer G, Vázquez O, Erb TJ. 2023

Sequence Information.Comments: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (40.48%) toMaximin 45K: 10%; R: 15%; G: 15%, I: 13%.Activity: active against E. coli (MIC 10.4 uM), B. subtilis (MIC 0.5 uM), A. baumannii clinical strain (MIC 0.8 uM), Enterobacter spp. (MIC 6.3 uM), K. pneumoniae DSM 30104 (MIC 25 uM), P-aeruginosa DSM 1117 (MIC >25 uM), S-aureus DSM 11729 MRSA (MIC >25 uM), and E. faecium (MIC 6.3 uM).Toxicity: Human RBC: HC50>250 uM, not hemo.lytic.
